metadata.description: TUDataset graph classification benchmarks for ISP-GNN evaluation (PREVIEW 5 per dataset)
metadata.source_paper: Morris et al., TUDataset: A collection of benchmark datasets for learning with graphs, arXiv:2007.08663

MUTAG.description: 188 mutagenic aromatic/heteroaromatic nitro compounds, binary mutagenicity classification

IMDB-BINARY.description: 1000 movie collaboration ego-networks, binary genre classification (Action vs Romance)

PTC_MR.description: 344 chemical compounds, binary carcinogenicity classification (male rats)

metadata.evaluation_protocol: Stratified 10-fold CV, report best epoch accuracy averaged over folds (GIN protocol)

source_papers.name: GIN
source_papers.title: How Powerful are Graph Neural Networks?

source_papers.name: GSN
source_papers.title: Improving Graph Neural Network Expressivity via Subgraph Isomorphism Counting

source_papers.name: PEARL
source_papers.title: Learning Efficient Positional Encodings with Graph Neural Networks
source_papers.note: PEARL results not available for MUTAG/PROTEINS/IMDB-BINARY/PTC_MR datasets. Evaluated on REDDIT-B/M and ZINC.
